<article>
    <h1>ExxonMo&#xAD;bil Asia Pac boss Gan Seow Kee to re&#xAD;tire</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201128/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-28"><time>2020-11-28</time></a>
        - <span>BUSINESS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Mr Gan Seow Kee’s roles as ExxonMo­bil Asia Pa­cific’s chair­man and man­ag­ing direc­tor will be taken over by its direc­tor Geraldine Chin.</p>
    <p>The chair­man and man­ag­ing direc­tor of ExxonMo­bil Asia Pa­cific, Mr Gan Seow Kee, will re­tire on Jan 1 next year after more than four decades with the com­pany.</p>
    <p>Tak­ing over the top jobs will be Ms Geraldine Chin, direc­tor of ExxonMo­bil Asia Pa­cific, the oil ma­jor said on Thurs­day.</p>
    <p>Mr Gan is also the pres­i­dent and direc­tor of ExxonMo­bil China Petroleum and Petro­chem­i­cal Com­pany, and serves as a direc­tor in Fu­jian Re­fin­ing and Petro­chem­i­cal Com­pany as well as Sinopec SenMei (Fu­jian) Petroleum Com­pany.</p>
    <p>He joined Esso Sin­ga­pore in 1979 and has held a va­ri­ety of roles in manufactur­ing, sales and mar­ket­ing, sup­ply and trad­ing, plan­ning as well as fi­nance, in Sin­ga­pore and the United States. This in­cluded lead­ing ExxonMo­bil’s global oil prod­ucts sup­ply and trad­ing business based in the US.</p>
    <p>Mr Gan joined Sin­ga­pore’s Coun­cil of Pres­i­den­tial Ad­vis­ers this year. He is also a vice-chair­man of the Sin­ga­pore Business Fed­er­a­tion and a board mem­ber of the Eco­nomic Devel­op­ment Board.</p>
    <p>Ms Chin joined ExxonMo­bil 32 years ago. The Sin­ga­porean has held po­si­tions in Sin­ga­pore and the US, in­clud­ing in sales and mar­ket­ing, sup­ply and trad­ing, hu­man re­sources and re­search.</p>
    <p>She is also a direc­tor of Sinopec SenMei (Fu­jian) Petroleum Com­pany.</p>

